      "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
      "Text": "Data description: https://doi.org/10.25919/j2af-ax46.\n \nDisclaimer: The creators, contributors, and distributors of the dataset shall not be held liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from the use of the dataset, including but not limited to, inaccuracies, errors, or omissions in the data.\nUnauthorized use or dissemination of this data is prohibited without explicit permission from the data owner. For further inquiries or permission requests, please contact Dr Julianne Lilley (julianne.lilley@csiro.au ).\n \nWhen citing this dataset, please use the following reference: Lilley, Julianne; Kirkegaard, John; Whish, Jeremy; Beletse, Yacob; Berger, Jens; Seymour, Mark; Bucat, Jackie; Herrmann, Chris; Dunn, Mathew; Ware, Andrew; Brill, Rohan; & Zhang, Heping (2024): Canola Agronomy. v3. CSIRO. Data Collection. https://doi.org/10.25919/j2af-ax46.\n\nWhen using the damage functions, please use the following reference for more information: Hu, P., He, D., Zheng, B., Whish, J., Kirkegaard, J., Bell, L., Leske, B., Chen, S., Uppal, R., Biddulph, B., Trethowan, R., Beletse, Y., Lilley, J., 2026. Event-based frost and heat damage functions improve yield predictions of APSIM canola and wheat: formulation, calibration, and evaluation. Agricultural and Forest Meteorology 386, 111239. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.agrformet.2026.111239",
      "Name": "Data Ownership Acknowledgement",
      "ResourceName": null,
      "Children": [],
      "Enabled": true,
      "ReadOnly": false
    },
